parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also lead to driver anxiety and stress, making it difficult to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly
the engine RPM increases rapidly without driver input
the vehicle takes off quickly without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent activation of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause sudden and unexpected changes in vehicle speed and stability, leading to reduced control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS system activates without any apparent reason
the ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle's brakes may pulse or vibrate
the vehicle's speed may suddenly decrease
the vehicle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire ply separation can lead to a sudden loss of tire pressure, causing the vehicle to lose control, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The tire may exhibit bulges or blisters on the sidewall
the tire may vibrate or shake while driving
the tire pressure monitoring system (TPMS) may illuminate
the tire may suddenly lose air pressure
the vehicle may pull to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature transmission failure can cause unexpected loss of power, stalling, or inability to shift gears, leading to accidents, strandings, or costly repairs.
symptoms: Transmission failure without warning
loss of power
stalling
inability to shift gears
unusual noises or vibrations
transmission slipping or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the defroster fan motor can cause poor visibility for the driver due to a fogged-up windshield, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The defroster fan motor fails to work
the heat vents do not blow out enough air to defrost the windshield
the windshield remains fogged up
reduced visibility while driving.
